    "body": "That was first discovered in https://github.com/scikit-learn/scikit-learn/issues/7645. \r\n\r\nI put together a stand-alone reproducing example:\r\n\r\n```cython\r\nfrom cpython cimport array\r\n\r\ncdef int n_iter = int(1e6)\r\n\r\ndef transform():\r\n    cdef array.array indices\r\n    indices = array.array(\"i\")\r\n\r\n    for i in range(n_iter):\r\n        array.resize_smart(indices, i + 1)\r\n```\r\n\r\nTiming it with 0.21.1 gives\r\n* 45ms with cython 0.21.1\r\n* 2.25s with cython 0.21.2\r\n\r\nNotebooks with the code and timings can be found [here](https://gist.github.com/lesteve/6f6956a0f8587c550339a54a1f912d14).\r\n\r\nNote that there is a speed regression on my Ubuntu machine as well which is a lot milder though (362 ms -> 456 ms for n_iter=1e7)\r\n\r\nSuggestions on how to improve the scikit-learn [code](https://github.com/scikit-learn/scikit-learn/blob/c336a4390ef93e65f4e6641b954524d9e412947f/sklearn/feature_extraction/_hashing.pyx) are more than welcome! ",
    "closed_at": "2016-10-18T18:35:47Z",
